# Skill Authoring

## Required files
Every skill directory MUST contain:
- `SKILL.md` — with valid frontmatter (`name`, `description`)
- `metadata.json` — with `version`, `author`, `date`, `abstract`

## SKILL.md constraints
- `name` field MUST match the directory name
- `description` max 1024 chars, third-person, includes WHAT + WHEN
- Body MUST be under 500 lines
- References one level deep only (SKILL.md → ref file, never ref → ref)

## metadata.json schema
```json
{
  "version": "semver",
  "author": "string",
  "date": "Month Year",
  "abstract": "One-line description",
  "references": ["optional array of URLs"]
}
```

## After any skill change
1. Ensure `metadata.json` version matches `skill-registry.json`
2. If adding a new skill: add entry to `skill-registry.json`
3. If the skill has `rules/`: rebuild AGENTS.md
4. Validate by running: `bash scripts/skill-sync.sh --list --skill=<name>`
